<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 14 at 1:25AM CDT until July 14 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN JACKSON...SOUTHERN HARMON...NORTHWESTERN FOARD AND
HARDEMAN COUNTIES...
At 125 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 3 miles west of Gould to 8 miles north of Quanah to 5
miles south of Goodlett, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Quanah, Eldorado, Goodlett, Copper Breaks State Park, and Lazare.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
